Quote:  (Griffiths Collection) ... I believe `crimping', in its proper light, is not known in the Province. Many of the bush settlers have, it is true, been deluded by these runaways, who describe themselves as newly-arrived immigrants. It is a certainty, too, that the sailors require no enticing ..
Notes: 1862 May 23 James Naughton, Commissioner of Police, Auckland Appendices to the Journals D-5

